-- South Africa November Monthly Budget Deficit 28.6 Billion Rand
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 2011-12-30T12:07:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-30/south-africa-november-monthly-budget-deficit-28-6-billion-rand.html
South Africa  posted a budget deficit
of 28.6 billion rand ($3.53 billion) in November, the National
Treasury said.  Government revenue was 50.8 billion rand last month, while
spending reached 79.4 billion rand, the Pretoria-based Treasury
said in a  statement  on its website today.  The budget deficit for the first eight months of the fiscal
year widened to 142.2 billion rand from 135 billion rand in the
same period a year ago, according to the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 